      "message": "Wouldn\u0027t it be simpler to:\ntake the strlen(to)\nreturn false if that\u0027s not equal to tagLen\nthen just return strncmp(to, tagStart, tagLen) !\u003d 0?\n\nAs it is, I found myself trying to figure out what happens if strlen(to) \u003c tagLen.  I guess it works because you\u0027re assuming there\u0027s no zeros in [tagStart, tagEnd), so they will compare different at the trailing zero of to?  But that\u0027s pretty involved reasoning.",
